Dashboard Overview

Welcome to the Complete Classifier Comparison Dashboard!

This interactive dashboard provides comprehensive visualization and comparison of multiple machine learning classifiers across various datasets.

Features:

  • Multiple Datasets: Various 2D and 3D datasets with different characteristics
  • 10 Classifiers: Including Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, Random Forest, SVM, k-NN, Neural Networks, and more
  • Interactive Visualizations: Rotate, zoom, and explore 3D plots
  • Performance Metrics: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1 Score, Training Time
  • Decision Boundaries: 2D and 3D visualizations of how classifiers separate classes
  • Confusion Matrices: Detailed classification performance analysis
  • Feature Importance: Understanding which features matter most
  • Cross-Validation: 5-fold CV accuracy with standard deviation

How to Use:

  1. Navigate between tabs using the menu above
  2. In Data Exploration, understand dataset characteristics
  3. In 2D/3D Visualizations, explore decision boundaries
  4. In Performance, compare classifier metrics
  5. Click on plots for interactive features (zoom, pan, hover)

Code Summary

Technologies Used:
  • Python Libraries: Scikit-learn, NumPy, Pandas, Plotly
  • Classifiers: 10 different algorithms
  • Datasets: 6 synthetic and real datasets
  • Visualization: 2D/3D interactive plots
About This Dashboard:

This dashboard was automatically generated by Python code that:

  1. Generates multiple datasets with different characteristics
  2. Trains 10 different classifiers on each dataset
  3. Evaluates performance using multiple metrics
  4. Creates interactive visualizations of decision boundaries
  5. Generates this HTML dashboard with all results

Complete Classifier Comparison Dashboard | Generated with Python, Scikit-learn & Plotly

Click and drag to rotate 3D plots | Hover over plots for details | Use tabs to navigate
